Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Belgrade, 22 Feb (TANJUG) -- Federal Assembly 
President Radoje Kontic has decided to appoint Nikola Sainovic, 
the hitherto president of the Government of Serbia, vice 
president of the federal government, the Federal Information 
Ministry reported today. 
  Sainovic will, in his capacity as vice president of the 
federal government, coordinate work on the implementation of a 
program for the reconstruction of the monetary system and the 
economic recovery of the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia. 
[passage omitted] 

